Knights of Sidonia and Majestic Prince follow the experiences of a group of mecha pilots as they fight to protect humanity against an alien race. In Knights of Sidonia, humanity has been reduced to fleeing in a colony ship following the destruction of Earth by aliens. The aliens are impossible to understand and cannot be communicated with. Every day of survival is a victory. In Majestic Prince, humanity has just started its fight to protect the Earth from invasion. The aliens have clear intentions and do not want any negotiation or peace. Every mission is a step closer to victory against this technologically superior race. Despite having humanity depend on you, the pilots in both series have dreams and hobbies like any other teenager.

entry.title: Isekai Maou to Shoukan Shoujo no Dorei Majutsu

data.content: This is the closest anime similar to Overlord that you can find for now. Similarities: - MCs of both anime are very powerful (OP although Iseaki Maou's MC Diablo is considered significantly weaker than Ainz and he has to rest to recover his mana after fights) and have a harem full of shawties. - MCs of both anime are trapped in a game (isekai) and don't want to get out. - In both anime, we listen to the inner voice of the main characters and there are lots of funny interactive scenes with the girls in the harem. The differences are: - In Overlord, Ainz has a game trait that limits his emotions, so he can be cruel and harsh, but in Isekai Maou, the main character takes a more lighthearted approach, forgiving almost all enemies (so this is the main difference, which can be a bit annoying). - In Overlord, the girls in the harem and Nazarick are the world's leading power, whereas the girls in Diablo's harem are powerless. - While Ainz has a policy of kingdom expansion, Diablo has a policy of travel. - While Overlord has a brutal and dark theme, Isekai Maou is a very light hearted anime.
